modules.description: Provides functions for implementing and verifying the KBB2017 protocol, including key exchange and message encryption operations. Works with cryptographic key pairs, session states, and encrypted message structures. Used to build secure communication channels with formal verification guarantees.

Handles cryptographic key exchange and message authentication using Diffie-Hellman and HMAC. Operates on byte sequences, public/private key pairs, and session tokens. Enables secure session establishment and integrity verification in peer-to-peer communication.
